<br>
I'm from the school of thought that believes that when the pet dies, so does the mage.  I'm slowly changing my mind though.  Enrage can buy enough time against ANY melee mob to resummon a new pet while at the same time doing much more damage than normal.  Maybe the new plan should be send in the pet and nuke like mad since many mobs don't summon.  When the enrages, we resummon (hitting pet get lost) and repeat until the mob is dead.  There are 2 keys to this working.  One, we must have a newer pet that enrages.. epic will not work clearly.  Two, is to make sure we have big enough mana pool.  As long as thats true we can pet cani back to full in less than 4 minutes once the fight is over.  The mage only needs a 61+ pet, and QS + EP AAs... not a lot.<br>
<br>
<br>
I'd like to point out that slow wouldn't make a huge difference if this works.  We have a lot of tools.  We need to use what we have before asking for more. <p>&lt;TABLE&gt;&lt;TR&gt;&lt;TD&gt;<br>
