<br>
In the past few days I've been steradily more and more able to gain groups, and more often than not am findingmyself grouped with another Mage as well. Our damage dealing 61+ is absolutely superb, and this is becoming common knowledge now.<br>
<br>
With that damage we bring (admitedly kinf of gimpy but it does the job) second-tier mana regen that stacks with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>everything</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and Call of the Hero. In Valor, I am constantly being told &quot;nice save Hog&quot; as time and again I tank the puller or a wayward group member out of trouble with a quick CoH. Indeed it was ironically enough a Shaman last night who said he has a new respect for Mages after he ran off with 3 mobs in tow after getting a KEI and suddenly found himself at 10% life thinking it was all over.<br>
<br>
I am entirely satisfied with my new role. As a true damage dealing class - arguably the best in the game - now that I can get groups I don't miss soloing. For me, it was always something I did when I coudln't get a group anyway, so I couldnt be happier with the way things worked out <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gallerus>Gallerus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 147<br> <font color=#333333>(11/12/02 6:30:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Slow &gt;&gt; All</span><hr size=1> &quot;Mages were not designed as soloers. The game itself was not designed for people to solo&quot;<br>
<br>
Mages WERE one of the classes that vi touted as being able to solo.  Saying otherwise is foolish, get your facts straight.  Is EQ a group orientated game ? yes.  Did they intend for some classes to be able to solo, YES, they said so themselves.  Regardless of their intentions, many classes that VI themselves didnt regard as solo classes have envolved into them due to spell lines / abilites that have been handed out.<br>
<br>
For those of you who say pop isnt meant to be soloable, please tell that to the bards, wizards, druids, rangers, sks, shaman, necros &amp; enchanters that I see soloing in pov every day!  That or get a clue cause youre clearly wrong &amp; dont know wtf youre talking about!<br>
<br>
Maybe only 3/15 classes get slows, but 8/15 get to solo in pov.  Any effective group in pop has a slower, anyone who says different is nuts.<br>
<br>
The fact of the matter is pop gimped mage solo power by rewarding classes that can mitigate damage through some means, mages mitigate damage with... uhm.. gate &amp; thats why we are far less powerful than we have ever been.  Anyone who cant see this fact is fooling themselves.  This is just the latest case of vi yanking mages around &amp; basically redefining their abilities in regards to how to play - i'm sure it was unintentional too, which is the really sad thing about this.  It doesnt impact me a ton because i've got a lot of friends - but I know a lotta people who play mages like really late at night/odd hours &amp; they have NEVER grouped...and now they are screwed completly since they can a) no longer solo &amp; b) either play at odd hours so cant get regular groups going, dont have contacts made to get into groups or a combination of the two.  I know several people who basically dont play anymore because of this &amp; I think its wrong.<br>
<br>
The worst part is VI has NO CLUE what the repercussions of their changes are - they made pop mobs &amp; tested them with standard xp groups &amp; declared everything ok.  They never bothered to look at the impact of mobs on classes that can solo through damage mitigation.  I'm sure it wasnt in the Vision(tm) for pop to have wizards quad kiting for obscene xp the 1st few weeks (and they can still do it now, just not as risk free as they could originally).  Hows about druids soloing with dc in places like pon getting, again, obscene xp at no risk?  Mages always come out on the short end of the stick because they solo through brute force. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32>Class Balance</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font>  <br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM AD SCRIPT -->
